        We propose the Lie-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> interpretation of poly-analytic functions in $L_2(\C,dμ)$, with the Gaussian measure $dμ$, based on a flag structure formed by the representation spaces of the $\mathfrak{sl}(2)$-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> realized by differential operators in $z$ and $\bar z$. Following the pattern of the one-dimensional sit&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.12771v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.12771v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
