      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.12771v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We propose the Lie-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> interpretation of poly-analytic functions in $L_2(\C,dμ)$, with the Gaussian measure $dμ$, based on a flag structure formed by the representation spaces of the $\mathfrak{sl}(2)$-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> realized by differential operators in $z$ and $\bar z$. Following the pattern of the one-dimensional situation, we define poly-Fock spaces in $d$ complex variables in a Lie-<span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> way, as the invariant spaces for the action of generators of a certain Lie <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span>. In addition to the basic case of the <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> $\mathfrak{sl}(d+1)$, we consider also the family of <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebras</span> $\mathfrak{sl}(m_1+1) \otimes \ldots \otimes \mathfrak{sl}(m_n+1)$ for tuples $\mathbf{m} = (m_1,m_2,\ldots,m_n)$ of positive integers whose sum is equal to $d$.
