    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11524v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;Ω_(B/V)(Ω_(B/k)) where R is either a complete regular local ring or a complete local normal domain with coefficient ring V (field k) and B is its integral closure in an <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> extension of Q(R). Similar problem is also studied over a normal domain R containing a field k of characteristic 0. In this connection new observations on the direct summand proper&hellip;
