    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        On the multipliers of the Figa-Talamanca Herz <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span>
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Derighetti%2C+A">Antoine Derighetti</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11378v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;, more precisely we show that the Banach <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> $A_p(G)$is a Banach module on $A_q(G).$
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11378v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.11378v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11378v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        Let $G$ be a locally compact group and $p,q\in \mathbb{R}$ with $p&gt;1$ $p\not=2$ and $q$ between $2$ and $p$ (if $p&lt;2$ then $p&lt;q&lt;2$, if $p&gt;2$ then $2&lt;q&lt;p.$) The main result of the paper is that $A_q(G)$ multiplies $A_p(G)$, more precisely we show that the Banach <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> $A_p(G)$is a Banach module on $A_q(G).$
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11378v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11378v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 21 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    

    

    
