    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Attaining Sudan&#39;s decoding radius with no genus penalty for <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> geometry codes
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Panaccione%2C+I">Isabella Panaccione</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11188v2-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        In this paper we present a decoding algorithm for <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> geometry codes with error-correcting capacity beyond half the designed distance of the code. This algorithm comes as a fusion of the Power Error Locating Pairs algorithm for <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> geometry codes and the technique used by Ehrhard in order to correct these c&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11188v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.11188v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11188v2-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper we present a decoding algorithm for <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> geometry codes with error-correcting capacity beyond half the designed distance of the code. This algorithm comes as a fusion of the Power Error Locating Pairs algorithm for <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> geometry codes and the technique used by Ehrhard in order to correct these codes up to half the designed distance. The decoding radius of this algorithm reaches that of Sudan algorithm, without any penalty given by the genus of the curve.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11188v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11188v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 23 March, 2021; <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">v1</span> submitted 20 March, 2021;
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
