    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        A priori bounds for quasi-linear SPDEs in the full sub-critical regime
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Otto%2C+F">Felix Otto</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Sauer%2C+J">Jonas Sauer</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Smith%2C+S">Scott Smith</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Weber%2C+H">Hendrik Weber</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11039v2-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;This allows us to capture additional symmetries which play a crucial role in our analysis. Assuming bounds on this model, which is modified in agreement with the concept of <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> renormalization, we prove local a priori estimates on solutions to the quasi-linear equations modified by the corresponding counter terms.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11039v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.11039v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.11039v2-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        This paper is concerned with quasi-linear parabolic equations driven by an additive forcing $ξ\in C^{α-2}$, in the full sub-critical regime $α\in (0,1)$. We are inspired by Hairer&#39;s regularity structures, however we work with a more parsimonious model indexed by multi-indices rather than trees. This allows us to capture additional symmetries which play a crucial role in our analysis. Assuming bounds on this model, which is modified in agreement with the concept of <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> renormalization, we prove local a priori estimates on solutions to the quasi-linear equations modified by the corresponding counter terms.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.11039v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.11039v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 25 March, 2021; <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">v1</span> submitted 19 March, 2021;
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
