        &hellip;topological relations among graphlets (graph elements) in rigorous mathematics language and from the perspective of graph encoding. We uncover, characterize and utilize <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebraic</span> and numerical relations in graphlet counts/frequencies. We present a novel algorithm for efficiently counting small subgraphs as a practical product of our theoretical findings.
