    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Conformal mechanics of homogeneously curved FRW cosmology: Möbius invariance, CVH <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> and relation to AdS$_2$
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Achour%2C+J+B">Jibril Ben Achour</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="search-hit">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.10700v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        &hellip;) Lie <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span>. The initial conditions of these evolving constant of motion form the CVH <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> which fully encodes the dynamics of the system. This structure reveals new dualities : on one hand, the cosmological dynamics can be reformulated as a particle propagating on the AdS$_2$ hyperboloid and on the other hand, on&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.10700v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.10700v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.10700v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We show that the homogeneously curved Friedmann-Robertson-Walker (FRW) cosmology filled with a massless scalar field enjoys a Noether symmetry under the 1d conformal group SL(2,$\mathbb{R}$). Concretely, the dynamics of the system is invariant under Möbius transformations of the proper time provided the scale factor transforms as a primary field. This extends previous results obtained recently for the flat FRW case, the (A)dS cosmology and the Kantowski-Sachs mini-superspace model. We compute the Noether charges generating this hidden conformal symmetry and show that they form an sl(2,$\mathbb{R}$) Lie <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span>. The initial conditions of these evolving constant of motion form the CVH <span class="search-hit mathjax">algebra</span> which fully encodes the dynamics of the system. This structure reveals new dualities : on one hand, the cosmological dynamics can be reformulated as a particle propagating on the AdS$_2$ hyperboloid and on the other hand, one can map the cosmological system onto conformal mechanics. These reformulations of the cosmological dynamics open up the possibility to import known results from these systems to classical and quantum cosmology.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.10700v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.10700v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 19 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="comments is-size-7">
